      "writtenOn": "2016-02-18T23:32:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do we really want to do this?\n\nThere are two problems with this:\n- Nothing\u0027s necessarily told the thread that the Thread object is being deleted, so it may not end at all.\n  - I agree that it\u0027s a programming error if that happens, but this will end up being a flakily failing assert, which will also manifest as a flaky delay in the emulator quitting (for instance).\n- The posix impl needs to also be updated to match this expectation.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 52,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 52,
        "endChar": 64
      },
      "revId": "d45b88b166f385043ef97d909d7344acb9c9e4fc",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "82b53dae_088aa708",
        "filename": "android/base/threads/Thread_win32.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 52,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-02-19T00:14:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1. if thread isn\u0027t done at this point, we delete the critical section and the thread dies painful death trying to lock it.\nassert() is a function to state expectations, this is exactly the place to do it.\nIt isn\u0027t a delay - it\u0027s just a very quick check if the thread is running\n2. this CL is for the win32 thread, posix to go next",
      "parentUuid": "c23655de_9bb0f70a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 52,
        "startChar": 8,
